You are building FaceShield — a triple-domain adversarial image protection system.

STACK:
- Backend: Python 3.10+, FastAPI, uvicorn, DeepFace, OpenCV, NumPy, SciPy, MediaPipe
- Frontend: React 18, Vite, Tailwind CSS
- Communication: REST API, base64 image transfer

ARCHITECTURE RULES:
- Layer 1 (`backend/services/layer1_pixel.py`): pixel-space adversarial noise only
- Layer 2 (`backend/services/layer2_frequency.py`): FFT frequency domain perturbation only
- Layer 3 (`backend/services/layer3_semantic.py`): MediaPipe landmark detection + weighted mask noise only
- `noise_composer.py`: orchestrates all 3 layers in sequence, returns per-layer metrics
- `deepface_probe.py`: runs `DeepFace.verify()` after each layer (each stage vs original), returns confidence at each stage

CODING RULES:
- Every function must have a docstring
- All image operations use numpy arrays internally
- base64 encode/decode only at API boundary in `backend/utils/image_utils.py`
- Never mix layer logic — keep each layer file independent
- Return confidence scores after every layer, not just final output
- API/shield errors: JSON body `{"error": "<message>"}` with HTTP 422

DEMO REQUIREMENT:
- `deepface_probe.py` must return a dict with keys:
  `original`, `after_layer1`, `after_layer2`, `after_layer3`
  (each value: e.g. `confidence_pct`, `raw`, optional `distance` / `verified` when DeepFace runs)
  so the frontend `ConfidenceTable` can show the four-row confidence drop table.
